   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Water Basins for 8,000 Villages using Solar Power</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Village residents plan and build a Rain Water Catchment Basin (RWCB) to have water all year round even in the dry torrid conditions of the Sahel.  With water, the transformation of villages from &apos;dry and dying&apos; to green and vibrant is amazing! The basin taps into the existing water aquifer, raises the water table, filling dry wells. Thanks to generous donations, two villages now have market days 3 days a week all year.</narrative>
  </description>
